0.5 FIVE YEAR ACCIDENT HISTORY

The Washington W. Va. site has an outstanding record of accident prevention which demonstrates its commitment to public and worker safety.  Even minor incidents are investigated to identify what went wrong and to learn how to prevent future occurrences.
The RMP requires that all incidents involving regulated chemicals that resulted in any off-site impact or significant on-site impacts are reported in this document.  During the previous five-year period, there were no such accidents at the GEAM Washington site.  

